                <div class="highlight">
                    <h3>Affordability Challenge</h3>
                    <p>Property prices have grown 3.5 times faster than the cost of living, creating a significant affordability gap for middle-income families. This trend indicates increasing financial burden for homebuyers.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="methodology">
                    <h3>Affordability Metrics</h3>
                    <p>• <strong>Price-to-Income Ratio:</strong> Has deteriorated from 3.2 (2001) to 9.4 (2024)</p>
                    <p>• <strong>EMI Burden:</strong> Increased from 25% to 45% of household income</p>
                    <p>• <strong>Down Payment:</strong> Required amount increased by 667% over study period</p>
                    <p>• <strong>Entry Barriers:</strong> First-time buyers face 3.5x higher financial requirements</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

